    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                <placeName>Pha</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>St Louis Mo.</placeName>
                <date>March 19th/5619</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Enclosed you find the opening address of <persName>Mr<lb/> I L
                    Moses</persName>, which you are respectfully requested to publish<lb/> together
                with mine (sent you last week) and <sic>preceeded</sic> by<lb/> the short
                Introduction I have hereby annexed or with such<lb/> remarks as you might think
                proper. <persName>Dr Illowy</persName> has declined<lb/> to hand us his address
                (:because another beautiful speech of his, which<lb/> he has requested to furnish
                for publication was not sent to you and for<lb/> such other reasons as are only
                printed:) Requesting you as<lb/>
                <add>?</add> in my last, to return the MS. in case you should not be<lb/> willing to
                publish it and with the assurance that this will not<lb/> offend us, though we would
                be pleased to see it published in your<lb/> valuable Occident I remain very
                respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Yours <persName role="author">Isidor Bush</persName></p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p>Editor Occident</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Pa</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
